<title>CHINA: Innovative Int'l year net down 29 pct.</title>
<headline>Innovative Int'l year net down 29 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-08-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   28.53	vs 43.41</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    5.6	  vs 10.3</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  11.36 loss vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    151.67     vs 213.73</p>
<p>    Turnover		     792.08     vs 638.20</p>
<p>    Company name		 Innovative International (Holdings) Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  September 3-11</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   October 9</p>
<p>NOTE - Innovative International is a car and cellular phone antenna manufacturer.</p>
<p>The company proposed a bonus issue of one 1999 warrant for every 10 shares held. One bonus 1999 warrant exercisable on or before August 31, 1999 at the price of HK$4 per share.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is 12.1 H.K. cents (including interim dividend of 6.5 cents) vs 15.1 cents.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
